Bird CLI + /last30days Skill Setup Guide
Complete guide for setting up Bird CLI and the /last30days Claude Code skill with proper authentication.

Prerequisites

Node.js/npm installed
Claude Code installed
Access to X/Twitter account
OpenAI API key (or compatible API like Z.ai)


Part 1: Install Bird CLI
1. Install Bird via npm
bashnpm install -g @steipete/bird
2. Authenticate Bird with X/Twitter
Bird uses cookie extraction from your browser. You need to be logged into X/Twitter in Chrome or Firefox.
Option A: Extract Cookies Manually (Recommended)
Step 1: Get your cookies while Chrome is running
bash# Install sqlite3 if not already installed
sudo apt install sqlite3

# Check if you're logged into X in Chrome
google-chrome https://x.com

# In a terminal, extract the cookie values
# Close Chrome first to unlock the database
pkill -9 chrome
sleep 2

# Extract auth_token
sqlite3 ~/.config/google-chrome/Default/Cookies "SELECT value FROM cookies WHERE name='auth_token' AND host_key='.x.com';"

# Extract ct0
sqlite3 ~/.config/google-chrome/Default/Cookies "SELECT value FROM cookies WHERE name='ct0' AND host_key='.x.com';"
Step 2: Set environment variables
bash# Add to .bashrc (replace with your actual cookie values)
cat >> ~/.bashrc << 'EOF'
# Bird CLI authentication
export AUTH_TOKEN="your_auth_token_value_here"
export CT0="your_ct0_value_here"
EOF

# Reload shell
source ~/.bashrc
Step 3: Verify Bird works
bash# Test authentication
bird whoami

# Should show your X/Twitter username and account info
Option B: Alternative Cookie Extraction via DevTools
If the sqlite3 method doesn't work:

Open Chrome and go to https://x.com (make sure you're logged in)
Press F12 to open DevTools
Go to: Application â†’ Cookies â†’ https://x.com
Find auth_token - right-click the Value â†’ Copy
Find ct0 - right-click the Value â†’ Copy
Use the values in the export commands above


Part 2: Install /last30days Skill
1. Clone the Repository
bash# Clone to Claude Code skills directory
git clone https://github.com/mvanhorn/last30days-skill.git ~/.claude/skills/last30days
2. Configure API Keys
Create the config directory and .env file:
bash# Create config directory
mkdir -p ~/.config/last30days

# Create .env file with your API keys
cat > ~/.config/last30days/.env << 'EOF'
# OpenAI API key (required for Reddit search)
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_key_here

# Optional: xAI API key for paid X search (if not using Bird CLI)
# XAI_API_KEY=xai-your-key-here
EOF

# Secure the file
chmod 600 ~/.config/last30days/.env
3. Add Bird CLI Environment Variables to .env
IMPORTANT: The /last30days skill needs to access the same Bird CLI credentials. Add them to the .env file:
bash# Add Bird CLI credentials to the skill's config
cat >> ~/.config/last30days/.env << 'EOF'

# Bird CLI authentication (for free X/Twitter search)
AUTH_TOKEN=your_auth_token_value_here
CT0=your_ct0_value_here
EOF
Complete .env file should look like:
bash# OpenAI API key (required for Reddit search)
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-key-here

# Bird CLI authentication (for free X/Twitter search)
AUTH_TOKEN=08e802c4221f08a9e1ffc6e05a447d9d8918196f
CT0=3344fa9a85bc5ec1023b63d6fe959932b643c780a011c0ee2b1e4323afa917f894aa001be2bea05016193fbb0f62c2b302a0a8df8dca1165bca9668ee5d9a82b3925fa7e243980cf3806995c9bbff875

# Optional: xAI API key (if not using Bird CLI)
# XAI_API_KEY=xai-your-key-here
4. Verify .env File
bash# Check the file exists and has correct permissions
ls -la ~/.config/last30days/.env

# Should show: -rw------- (600 permissions)

# View contents (verify your keys are there)
cat ~/.config/last30days/.env

Part 3: Fix the API Errors
Based on your error messages, here's what needs to be fixed:
Error 1: OpenAI API 401 Unauthorized
[REDDIT ERROR] OpenAI API error: HTTP 401: Unauthorized
Cause: Your OpenAI API key in .env is invalid or expired.
Fix:
bash# Edit the .env file
nano ~/.config/last30days/.env

# Update the OPENAI_API_KEY line with a valid key
# If using Z.ai (as shown in your earlier setup):
OPENAI_API_KEY=d747f216d4434754af9ff1672ecf261f.ISELcv9prVdsewyj

# Or get a new OpenAI key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys

# Save and exit (Ctrl+X, then Y, then Enter)
Error 2: No X/Twitter Data
ðŸ’¡ Tip: For X/Twitter data with real likes & reposts:
   FREE: npm install -g @steipete/bird (uses browser session)
Cause: Bird CLI credentials are not available to the skill.
Fix: You already added AUTH_TOKEN and CT0 to the .env file in step 3 above. Verify they're there:
bash# Check if Bird credentials are in the .env file
grep -E "AUTH_TOKEN|CT0" ~/.config/last30days/.env

# Should show both variables with values

Part 4: Test the Setup
1. Test Bird CLI Standalone
bash# Should work from terminal
bird whoami
bird search "test query" -n 3
2. Test /last30days in Claude Code
Open Claude Code and try:
/last30days What are the best rap songs lately
Expected behavior:

Should search Reddit (if OpenAI key is valid)
Should search X/Twitter (if Bird credentials are in .env)
Should provide synthesized results

3. Check for Specific Issues
If it still doesn't work, check:
bash# Verify Bird can be found by the skill
which bird

# Should output: /usr/local/bin/bird or similar

# Check if environment variables are exported
env | grep -E "AUTH_TOKEN|CT0"

# Should show both variables with values

Complete .env File Template
Here's what your ~/.config/last30days/.env should contain:
bash# ============================================
# /last30days Skill Configuration
# ============================================

# ----------------
# OpenAI API (Required for Reddit search)
# ----------------
# Get from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Or use Z.ai compatible endpoint
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_key_here

# Optional: If using Z.ai or other OpenAI-compatible API
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.z.ai/api/paas/v4

# ----------------
# X/Twitter Search (Choose one method)
# ----------------

# Method 1: Bird CLI (Free - Recommended)
# Get these from Chrome cookies (see instructions above)
AUTH_TOKEN=your_auth_token_from_chrome
CT0=your_ct0_token_from_chrome

# Method 2: xAI API (Paid alternative to Bird)
# Get from: https://console.x.ai/
# XAI_API_KEY=xai-your-key-here

# ============================================
# Notes:
# - At least one of (Bird CLI credentials OR xAI key) required for X search
# - Bird CLI is preferred (free, no rate limits)
# - OpenAI key is required for Reddit search
# ============================================

Troubleshooting
Issue: "REDDIT ERROR: HTTP 401: Unauthorized"
Solution:

Check your OpenAI API key is valid
If using Z.ai, make sure OPENAI_BASE_URL is set correctly
Verify the key has credits/quota remaining

bash# Test your OpenAI key directly
curl https://api.openai.com/v1/models \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_OPENAI_API_KEY"

# Should return a list of models, not an error
Issue: "No X/Twitter data"
Solution:

Verify Bird CLI works standalone: bird whoami
Check AUTH_TOKEN and CT0 are in ~/.config/last30days/.env
Make sure the values are not wrapped in quotes in .env (or use single quotes)

bash# Good:
AUTH_TOKEN=abc123def456
# Or:
AUTH_TOKEN='abc123def456'

# Bad:
AUTH_TOKEN="abc123def456"  # May cause issues
Issue: Bird says "database is locked"
Solution: Close Chrome before extracting cookies
bashpkill -9 chrome
sleep 2
# Then run your sqlite3 commands
Issue: Cookies are encrypted
Solution: Use the manual DevTools extraction method instead of sqlite3
Issue: /last30days command not found in Claude Code
Solution:

Verify the skill is installed: ls -la ~/.claude/skills/last30days
Restart Claude Code
Check if other skills work (try /help or other slash commands)


Quick Reference
Bird CLI Commands
bashbird whoami                    # Show authenticated account
bird search "query" -n 10      # Search tweets
bird --version                 # Check version
/last30days Commands (in Claude Code)
bash/last30days [topic]                    # Basic research
/last30days [topic] --days=7           # Last 7 days only
/last30days [topic] --quick            # Faster, fewer sources
/last30days [topic] --deep             # More comprehensive
/last30days [topic] --sources=reddit   # Reddit only
/last30days [topic] --sources=x        # X/Twitter only
Important File Paths

Bird config: ~/.config/bird/config.json5 (optional)
Bird credentials: ~/.bashrc (AUTH_TOKEN and CT0 exports)
Skill config: ~/.config/last30days/.env
Skill location: ~/.claude/skills/last30days
Chrome cookies: ~/.config/google-chrome/Default/Cookies


Summary of What You Need
âœ… For Reddit search:

Valid OpenAI API key in ~/.config/last30days/.env

âœ… For X/Twitter search (choose one):

Option A: Bird CLI installed + AUTH_TOKEN and CT0 in both ~/.bashrc AND ~/.config/last30days/.env
Option B: xAI API key in ~/.config/last30days/.env

âœ… For both to work:

All credentials in ~/.config/last30days/.env
File permissions set to 600
Claude Code restarted after configuration


Testing Checklist
Run through this checklist to verify everything works:

 Bird CLI installed: bird --version
 Bird authenticated: bird whoami shows your X username
 Environment variables set: env | grep -E "AUTH_TOKEN|CT0" shows values
 .env file exists: ls -la ~/.config/last30days/.env
 .env file has OpenAI key: grep OPENAI_API_KEY ~/.config/last30days/.env
 .env file has Bird credentials: grep -E "AUTH_TOKEN|CT0" ~/.config/last30days/.env
 Skill installed: ls -la ~/.claude/skills/last30days
 Test in Claude Code: /last30days test query

If all checkboxes pass, the skill should work!

Getting Help
If you still have issues:

Check the Bird CLI GitHub: https://github.com/steipete/bird
Check the /last30days GitHub: https://github.com/mvanhorn/last30days-skill
File an issue with:

Output of bird whoami
Output of env | grep -E "AUTH_TOKEN|CT0|OPENAI"
Contents of ~/.config/last30days/.env (redact actual key values)
Full error message from Claude Code




